Besides GSH, ascorbic acid (AA) and N-acetyl-l-cysteine (NAC) are also nonenzymatic types of antioxidants. They also showed similar effect to recover the fluorescence of the Pdots-ClO− system (Fig. 3
                        ). The fluorescence intensity increased with the increase of concentration of the antioxidants. The same phenomenon was observed with enzymatic antioxidants (i.e., SOD and CAT) as well. As shown in Fig. 4
                        , the fluorescence intensity of Pdots-ClO− system linearly increased as the concentration of SOD and CAT increased, which suggested that SOD and CAT also reversibly reduced the oxidized hydroxyl group in the surface of CCP-HA Pdots. According to the results of CCP-HA Pdots for detecting antioxidants, linear equation, square of correlation coefficients (R2), linear concentration ranges and detection limit were summarized from various antioxidants including GSH, AA, NAC, SOD and CAT (Table 2
                        ).
